-- Fujifilm Says It Made Proposal to Olympus Financial Adviser on Investments
-- B y   N a o k o   F u j i m u r a
-- 2012-01-30T07:01:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/fujifilm-says-it-made-proposal-to-olympus-financial-adviser-on-investments.html
Fujifilm Holdings Corp. (4901)  proposed a
partnership with  Olympus Corp. (7733) , the Japanese camera and
endoscope maker beset by an accounting scandal, and may invest
in the company, Shigehiro Nakajima, Fujifulm executive vice
president, said at a press conference in Tokyo today.  The plan was presented to Olympus adviser SMBC Nikko
Securities Inc., Nakajima said. The companies may also exchange
executives, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naoko Fujimura in Tokyo at 
 nfujimura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dave McCombs at 
 dmccombs@bloomberg.net  